Heating curve: First we pelleted Nb -- I used a surplus of Nb powder so if we lost mass we would still be able to have a piece big enough for powder and PPMS. Boron is supposedly difficult to arc melt but we just put it under the other materials and it melted fine. Initial melt, flip/melt (had to take arc-melter apart here as a B piece scattered, so I flipped after putting the B near the sample again), flip/melt, flip/melt. Try to use lowest current as possible. Wait for humming as we turn current up to max of 2, then ~10-20 sec more of melt.